==Translingual==
===Etymology===
formed from the family name ''Dipsacaceae''

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''''Dipsacales'''''
# {{botany}} a [[botanical name]] at the rank of order. [[Circumscription]] and placement of the order will depend on [[taxonomic system]] or viewpoint. As accepted by the APG II system (2003) this order is placed in the [[clade]] '''asterids''' (in the '''euasterids II''', to be precise). In the earlier Cronquist system (1981) the order was placed in the subclass ''Asteridae'' of class ''Magnoliopsida''.

